addr="jms-00RN"
type="local">Baby steps in higher domain theory</fr:link> › the Phoa principle <fr:em>vs.</fr:em> synthetic quasicoherence</fr:title><fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The higher Phoa principle is a Kock–Lawvere / <fr:em><fr:link
href="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh.xml"
title="A general Nullstellensatz for generalized spaces"
addr="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh"
type="local">“synthetic quasi-coherence”</fr:link></fr:em> axiom that comes directly from the geometric theory of a strict interval, as a quotient of the theory of bounded distributive lattices (<fr:link
href="danielgratzer.xml"
title="Daniel Gratzer"
addr="danielgratzer"
type="local">Gratzer</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>Question.</fr:strong> What are the other domain theoretic consequences of synthetic quasicoherence?</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
