text="Synthetic quasicoherence">Synthetic quasicoherence</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon><fr:meta
name="source">Theorem 4.10 <fr:link
href="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh.xml"
title="A general Nullstellensatz for generalized spaces"
addr="blechschmidt-2023-qcoh"
type="local">Blechschmidt</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex> be a horn theory. The generic <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex>-model <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>quasicoherent</fr:em> in the following sense: internal to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Set}{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathbb {T}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, for any finitely presentable <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>-algebra <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, the canonical <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>-algebra homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A \to  U_{\mathbb {T}}^{\operatorname {Spec}{A}}]]></fr:tex> sending <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  f:\operatorname {Spec}{A}. f\,a]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}{A}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link
href="jms-008U.xml"
title="Spectrum of an algebra"
addr="jms-008U"
type="local">synthetic spectrum</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
